At GYS, our vision is in our name, Got Your Six. We got your back. We got you. We got all of you. We are glad you are back home and want to show you how much we got have your back. We will not let you become a statistic. We will not let you feel alone. We will not let you remain vulnerable. We want you to have the mental health services you need and deserve. For as long as you need them.
Florida is the third largest population in the nation after California and Texas with roughly 1.5 million veterans.
69,000 active duty military personally reside in Florida, the 6th largest population in the nation
The three most common mental health concerns for veterans are Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD), depression and Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI).

section_title: Veterans more susceptible to mental health concerns
section_text: The rate of major depression among Veterans is 5x as high as civilians, while the rate of PTSD is nearly 15x higher.
GYS is here to serve our service members by supporting them, their families, & friends with tools & resources to assist in transitioning our heroes home
Monthly Events, educational resources, partnered perks, and much more to come for our heroes to get the help and support they need to effectively transition home from their service.
Our greatest allies in successfully helping truly make our heroes feel at home again, we will provide tools and resources in order to help navigate the process of supporting a veteran in need.

GYS wants to help veterans know our mission begins when theirs' ends. With every shirt or product purchase, you can help raise awareness of Veterans mental health while empowering our local community to be armed with the knowledge, compassion, and courage to complete our mission, to save veteran lives. By these purchases on our website or at our local pop-ups, you can help us invest directly into mental health services for our veterans.

section_subtitle: To SAY and SHOW, we Golf Yankee Six.
section_text: Golf Yankee Six is a movement dedicated to creating awareness of veteran’s mental health and finding help for veterans’ struggling with depression, PTSD, and suicide in Orlando, Florida. We started to encourage, educate, and invest directly into mental health services for our veterans. Use your voice to start a conversation, create hope, and show your support for our veterans. If you want to support our mission, you can get involved by following us on Facebook & Instagram, attending our events, buying our American-made merchandise, or sharing resources from our website with a loved one.

We are two women with a goal to change the mental health world, specifically for our service men and women. As mental health practitioners, with 30 years combined experience and 15 years of friendship, we knew we could make a difference. We specialize in trauma, Post-traumatic Stress Disorder, and veterans returning from combat. We have a specific passion to change the lives of our veterans, one soldier at a time. What they see and experience is our motivation to never give up on them. Ever.
We hold these near and dear to our hearts
